3.  **Court Acquits Chienge MP Given Katuta of Threat Charge**
    Lusaka magistrate Idah Phiri acquitted Chienge Member of Parliament Given Katuta of threatening violence against a Times of Zambia photographer, Henry Chunza, stating the prosecution failed to prove the allegations met the legal threshold; the court expressed difficulty understanding why the case proceeded given the "weak" and absent "cogent and credible evidence," highlighting the importance of robust legal standards in our justice system. Ms. Katuta, who stated she viewed the case as a "political push," was freed after the verdict.

